Sec. 54.006. INVESTMENT BY OTHER CORPORATIONS. After obtaining
the approval of the banking commissioner, any corporation organized
under the laws of this state other than a savings bank may invest any
part of its money in the preferred stock of a corporation formed
under this chapter.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1120, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

